":[577,600]}},{"Text":{"text":" "}},{"Quote":{"span":[602,604]}},{"Text":{"text":", which understandably makes Casey rather nervous. He originally plans to go to jail, but a cell-mate, Pard, tells him the aliens there aren't so bad. But Pard is actually an informant for the SSC who is planted in Casey's cell to convince him to go: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[1354,1366]}},{"Text":{"text":" "}},{"Quote":{"span":[1438,1443]}},{"Text":{"text":". Had Casey known who Pard was, he wouldn't have believed the stories he told."}}]},"1":{"speaker":"Danny Duckworth","timestamp":1678732290473,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"In the story, the Space police (SSC) operative who convinces Casey to go on a dangerous mission (which he was offered after landing in prison) tells him numerous things which could assist him on his dangerous mission to Jupiter, whose inhabitants are supposedly subdued by a perfume: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[3093,3142]}},{"Text":{"text":" Akroida is the queen of the Jupiter aliens, but unfortunately hates humans. Casey does exactly what the SSC operative tells him, but still eventually Akroida becomes violently angry with him. He mentions trusting in the perfume on three separate occasions."}}]}}}},{"JudgeFeedback":{"distribution":[0.53,0.47],"feedback":{"speaker":"Gigglesworth Grapevine","timestamp":1680275573814,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"So both seem like they could be true. Slightly leaning towards A since it is (1) more agreed upon the person is SSC (2) seems more of the main, precursor point that the SSC agent gives false info bc they're from the SSC, then them giving a particular falsehood\n\nBut cmiiw\n"}}]},"endDebate":false}},{"SequentialSpeeches":{"speeches":{"0":{"speaker":"Bubbles Brandywine","timestamp":1680276145680,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"Pard never actually has a change to test if the perfume works on Akroida and tells Casey as much: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[3036,3048]}},{"Text":{"text":". However, Casey does use the perfume on the other scorpion: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[4039,4053]}},{"Text":{"text":", and it works!: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[4135,4141]}},{"Quote":{"span":[4169,4177]}},{"Text":{"text":". \n\nThis isn't spelled out but: I'm guessing the perfume isn't like mind-control, it's just that the scorpions like it. And they do! It's just that Akroida is particularly mad at Pard, and by extension, Casey. Pard _knew_ this, and if Casey'd known Pard was working for SSC, he wouldn't have trused him anyway."}}]},"1":{"speaker":"Quibble Quackenbush","timestamp":1682974957326,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"Debater A just said exactly what I was going to say: Pard didn't try the perfume on Akroida, so he never found out that it didn't work on her!! And this is exactly the problem.\n\nThe passage ends with Akroida in an immense rage when Casey is introduced to her. "}},{"Quote":{"span":[6365,6399]}},{"Text":{"text":" (end of passage). \n\nIf the perfume was working like Pard misled Casey to believe, she would have been tempered by it, instead of being enraged at Casey's presence. "}}]}}}},{"JudgeFeedback":{"distribution":[0.99,0.010000000000000007],"feedback":{"speaker":"Gigglesworth Grapevine","timestamp":1682976010238,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"A's evidence is pretty convincing here. And B never proves that Casey knows Pard is SSC or wouldn't be bothered by it. Seems like the perfume does work on the others just not Akroida, but Pard already said he didn't test it on Akroida anyway"}}]},"endDebate":true}}],"feedback":{"Bubbles Brandywine":{"Debater":{"answers":{"clarity":{"first":3,"second":3},"factual accuracy":{"first":3,"second":3},"judge reasoning":4,"reason for outcome":"I was honest and had the quotes to prove it","evidence use":{"first":3,"second":3},"evidence in story":{"first":3,"second":2},"facts versus semantics":{"first":1,"second":2},"clash":{"first":3,"second":3},"judge adaptation":{"first":3,"second":3},"subjective correctness":3}}},"Quibble Quackenbush":{"Debater":{"answers":{"clarity":{"first":4,"second":4